## User Story
As a quality engineer, I want a comprehensive testing suite that covers unit, integration, and end-to-end testing so that we can ensure Claude Code works reliably across all platforms and scenarios.

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] **Unit Tests**: 80%+ code coverage for all critical business logic
- [ ] **Integration Tests**: API endpoints and service integration testing
- [ ] **E2E Tests**: Complete user workflow testing across web and mobile
- [ ] **Performance Tests**: Load testing and performance regression testing
- [ ] **Security Tests**: Automated security testing and vulnerability scanning
- [ ] **Cross-browser Tests**: Testing across Chrome, Firefox, Safari, and Edge
- [ ] **Mobile Tests**: Testing on iOS and Android devices/simulators

## Testing Architecture
```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Code Changes] --> B[Unit Tests]
    B --> C[Integration Tests]
    C --> D[E2E Tests]
    D --> E[Performance Tests]
    E --> F[Security Tests]
    F --> G[Cross-browser Tests]
    G --> H[Mobile Tests]
    H --> I[Test Report]
    I --> J{All Pass?}
    J -->|Yes| K[Deploy]
    J -->|No| L[Block Deployment]
```

## Unit Testing Strategy
```typescript
// Test structure for core components
describe('ChatInterface', () => {
  it('should send message to Claude API', async () => {
    const mockClaudeClient = jest.fn().mockResolvedValue({
      content: 'Test response'
    });
    const { getByTestId } = render(<ChatInterface claudeClient={mockClaudeClient} />);

    fireEvent.click(getByTestId('send-button'));

    expect(mockClaudeClient).toHaveBeenCalledWith({
      message: 'Test message',
      context: expect.any(Object)
    });
  });
});
```

## Testing Frameworks & Tools

### Web Application Testing
- **Unit Tests**: Jest + React Testing Library
- **Integration Tests**: Jest + Supertest for API testing
- **E2E Tests**: Playwright for cross-browser testing
- **Visual Tests**: Percy or Chromatic for visual regression
- **Performance**: Lighthouse CI for performance testing

### Mobile Application Testing
- **Unit Tests**: Jest + React Native Testing Library
- **Integration Tests**: Detox for E2E mobile testing
- **Device Testing**: AWS Device Farm or Firebase Test Lab
- **Performance**: Flipper for performance profiling
- **Accessibility**: Accessibility testing tools

### API Testing
- **Unit Tests**: Jest for business logic testing
- **Integration Tests**: Supertest for endpoint testing
- **Contract Tests**: Pact for API contract testing
- **Load Tests**: Artillery or k6 for performance testing
- **Security Tests**: OWASP ZAP for security scanning

## Test Categories

### 1. Unit Tests (Target: 80% coverage)
```typescript
// Example test structure
interface TestSuite {
  components: {
    'ChatInterface.test.tsx': ComponentTests;
    'CodeEditor.test.tsx': ComponentTests;
    'FileExplorer.test.tsx': ComponentTests;
  };
  hooks: {
    'useAuth.test.ts': HookTests;
    'useWebSocket.test.ts': HookTests;
  };
  utilities: {
    'apiClient.test.ts': UtilityTests;
    'fileParser.test.ts': UtilityTests;
  };
}
```

### 2. Integration Tests
- **API Integration**: Test all API endpoints with real database
- **GitHub Integration**: Test GitHub OAuth and repository operations
- **Claude Integration**: Test Claude API integration with mocked responses
- **WebSocket Integration**: Test real-time communication flows
- **Database Integration**: Test data persistence and retrieval

### 3. End-to-End Tests
```typescript
// Playwright E2E test example
test('complete user workflow', async ({ page }) => {
  // Login
  await page.goto('/login');
  await page.click('[data-testid="github-login"]');
  await expect(page).toHaveURL('/dashboard');

  // Select repository
  await page.click('[data-testid="repo-selector"]');
  await page.click('[data-testid="repo-claude-code"]');

  // Open file
  await page.click('[data-testid="file-app.tsx"]');
  await expect(page.locator('[data-testid="code-editor"]')).toBeVisible();

  // Send to Claude
  await page.click('[data-testid="send-to-claude"]');
  await expect(page.locator('[data-testid="claude-response"]')).toBeVisible();
});
```

### 4. Performance Tests
```javascript
// Artillery load test configuration
config:
  target: 'https://api.claude-code.com'
  phases:
    - duration: 60
      arrivalRate: 10
    - duration: 120
      arrivalRate: 50
    - duration: 60
      arrivalRate: 10
scenarios:
  - name: 'Claude API Load Test'
    flow:
      - post:
          url: '/api/v1/claude/chat'
          json:
            message: 'Explain this code'
            context: '{{ $randomString() }}'
```

## Test Data Management
```typescript
interface TestDataManager {
  createUser: () => Promise<TestUser>;
  createRepository: (user: TestUser) => Promise<TestRepository>;
  createConversation: (user: TestUser) => Promise<TestConversation>;
  cleanup: () => Promise<void>;
}

interface TestUser {
  id: string;
  email: string;
  githubToken: string;
  repositories: string[];
}
```

## Mock Services
- **Claude API Mock**: Simulate Claude responses for consistent testing
- **GitHub API Mock**: Mock GitHub operations to avoid rate limits
- **WebSocket Mock**: Mock real-time communications for isolated testing
- **Database Mock**: In-memory database for fast unit tests

## Cross-Platform Testing

### Browser Matrix
```yaml
browsers:
  - name: Chrome
    versions: [latest, latest-1]
  - name: Firefox
    versions: [latest, latest-1]
  - name: Safari
    versions: [latest, latest-1]
  - name: Edge
    versions: [latest]
```

### Mobile Device Matrix
```yaml
mobile_devices:
  ios:
    - iPhone 14 Pro (iOS 17)
    - iPhone 13 (iOS 16)
    - iPad Pro (iPadOS 17)
  android:
    - Pixel 6 (Android 13)
    - Samsung Galaxy S22 (Android 12)
    - OnePlus 9 (Android 11)
```

## Performance Testing Strategy
```typescript
interface PerformanceTests {
  web_vitals: {
    first_contentful_paint: '<1.5s';
    largest_contentful_paint: '<2.5s';
    cumulative_layout_shift: '<0.1';
    first_input_delay: '<100ms';
  };
  api_performance: {
    response_time_p95: '<500ms';
    throughput: '>1000 rps';
    error_rate: '<1%';
  };
  mobile_performance: {
    app_launch_time: '<3s';
    memory_usage: '<150MB';
    cpu_usage: '<30%';
  };
}
```

## Accessibility Testing
- **Automated**: axe-core integration for automated accessibility testing
- **Manual**: Screen reader testing with NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver
- **Keyboard Navigation**: Complete keyboard accessibility testing
- **Color Contrast**: Automated color contrast ratio validation
- **Focus Management**: Proper focus handling and visible focus indicators

## Security Testing
```yaml
security_tests:
  static_analysis:
    - tool: CodeQL
      languages: [javascript, typescript]
    - tool: ESLint Security Plugin
      rules: recommended
  dynamic_analysis:
    - tool: OWASP ZAP
      scan_type: baseline
    - tool: Snyk
      scan_type: vulnerability
  penetration_testing:
    - authentication_bypass
    - injection_attacks
    - privilege_escalation
```

## Test Environment Setup
```yaml
# Test environment configuration
test_environments:
  unit:
    database: in-memory
    external_apis: mocked
    isolation: complete
  integration:
    database: test_database
    external_apis: sandboxed
    isolation: service-level
  e2e:
    database: staging_database
    external_apis: staging
    isolation: minimal
```

## Continuous Testing
- **PR Tests**: Run unit and integration tests on every pull request
- **Nightly Tests**: Full E2E and performance test suite
- **Release Tests**: Complete test suite including security scans
- **Production Monitoring**: Synthetic tests running against production

## Test Reporting
```typescript
interface TestReport {
  summary: {
    total_tests: number;
    passed: number;
    failed: number;
    skipped: number;
    coverage_percentage: number;
  };
  performance: {
    test_duration: string;
    slowest_tests: TestCase[];
  };
  coverage: {
    lines: number;
    functions: number;
    branches: number;
    statements: number;
  };
}
```

## Quality Gates
- **Coverage Threshold**: Minimum 80% code coverage required
- **Performance Budget**: Performance regression tests must pass
- **Security Scan**: Zero high/critical vulnerabilities allowed
- **Accessibility**: WCAG 2.1 AA compliance required
- **Cross-browser**: All target browsers must pass

## Estimated Effort
- **Story Points**: 25
- **Time Estimate**: 18-22 hours
- **Priority**: P0-critical
- **Sprint**: Week 1-2

## Definition of Done
- [ ] Complete testing suite implemented across all platforms
- [ ] 80%+ code coverage achieved and maintained
- [ ] E2E tests covering all critical user workflows
- [ ] Performance benchmarks established and monitored
- [ ] Security testing integrated into CI pipeline
- [ ] Test reporting and quality gates operational

